node: refuse_blame | The Last Returned
  *(It is quiet for a long moment, and Garrow's certainty seems to steady it from across the room.)* ...You're right that it's too big to be one person's fault. *(slowly)* But it might be exactly the right size to be one person's *responsibility* — which is a different thing, kinder and harder. Not "this is your fault." "This is yours to mend." *(it meets your eyes)* I could never tell the two apart. Maybe that's why I'm still here. Maybe you can.
