node: choose | The Last Returned
  *(It steps back, finally, into the dark it came from — not vanishing, but *yielding*, the way an author sets down a finished page.)* The room is yours now, and every power in it, and every era, and the pen. *(your own voice, at peace for the first time in ten thousand years)* Break it. Complete it. Rewrite it. Seize it. Or walk away from all of it. I cannot predict which — and do you understand what a *gift* that is, after ten thousand years of knowing every ending? *(softly)* Surprise me. Surprise us. Surprise the grief itself. We have all waited so long to be surprised.
