node: verdict | Jergal
  *(You reach, for an instant, for the easy thing — the verdict, the rule, the *Faithless, next* — and the ledger seems to flinch under your pen.)* Ah. You felt the pull of it — the rule, the shortcut, the comfortable cruelty. *(without reproach)* Do not be ashamed; it is the oldest pull there is, and I gave in to it for ten thousand years. The verdict is easy. The *attention* is the mercy. Set the rule down, crack, and read the next name slowly — as a person, not a sum. Try again. The dead have waited; they can wait while you learn to look.
